# Browser error monitoring. The real DSN lives in Bitwarden as
# AUT_SENTRY_WEB_DSN and is injected only for production builds.
# This value is intentionally public at runtime (Sentry DSNs identify a
# project; they are not authentication credentials), but must never be
# committed here.
PUBLIC_AUT_SENTRY_WEB_DSN=

# The site is a static Astro export, with no server/API runtime to instrument.
# AUT_SENTRY_API_DSN is therefore intentionally not provisioned. If a server
# runtime or source-map upload is introduced later, add its credentials in
# Bitwarden first; do not add real values to an .env file.
